access-tutorial-name = Access, doors, and navigation
access-tutorial-tooltip = Learn how your ID card affects doors and how to find an alternate route.

access-tut-welcome-bubble = Learn how ID access, detours, bolts, and signal controls affect airlocks.
access-tut-welcome-chat = This tutorial shows why some airlocks open, why others deny access, and how to find a safe route when the direct path is blocked.
access-tut-welcome-tts = This tutorial shows why some airlocks open, why others deny access, and how to find a safe route when the direct path is blocked.

access-tut-id-card-bubble = Examine your ID card with [tutkeybind="ExamineEntity"].
access-tut-id-card-chat = This is your ID card. It stores your job and access; while it stays in the ID slot, door readers check it automatically.
access-tut-id-card-tts = This is your ID card. It stores your job and access; while it stays in the ID slot, door readers check it automatically.

access-tut-open-normal-door-bubble = Open the ordinary door with [tutkeybind="UIClick"].
access-tut-open-normal-door-chat = An ordinary door does not require special access and opens for any crew member.
access-tut-open-normal-door-tts = An ordinary door does not require special access and opens for any crew member.

access-tut-try-restricted-door-bubble = Try to open this door with [tutkeybind="UIClick"].
access-tut-try-restricted-door-chat = The door stays closed: your ID card does not have command access. Trying the door is still useful because it shows why access was denied.
access-tut-try-restricted-door-tts = The door stays closed: your ID card does not have command access. Trying the door is still useful because it shows why access was denied.

access-tut-open-authorized-door-bubble = This engineering door accepts your ID card. Open it with [tutkeybind="UIClick"].
access-tut-open-authorized-door-chat = Different doors require different access. Your card has engineering access, so this airlock opens for you.
access-tut-open-authorized-door-tts = Different doors require different access. Your card has engineering access, so this airlock opens for you.

access-tut-closed-route-bubble = Reach the closed route.
access-tut-closed-route-chat = The direct path ends at a closed door. Not every obstacle needs force; look for another route first.
access-tut-closed-route-tts = The direct path ends at a closed door. Not every obstacle needs force; look for another route first.

access-tut-find-detour-bubble = Follow the next green marker and find the detour.
access-tut-find-detour-chat = Markers help you navigate unfamiliar parts of the station. A detour may lead to a door your ID card can open.
access-tut-find-detour-tts = Markers help you navigate unfamiliar parts of the station. A detour may lead to a door your ID card can open.

access-tut-open-alternative-door-bubble = Open the alternative passage door with [tutkeybind="UIClick"].
access-tut-open-alternative-door-chat = You found an alternate route. On the station, check side corridors and maintenance passages when the direct path is closed.
access-tut-open-alternative-door-tts = You found an alternate route. On the station, check side corridors and maintenance passages when the direct path is closed.

access-tut-try-bolted-door-bubble = Try to open this door with [tutkeybind="UIClick"].
access-tut-try-bolted-door-chat = The door stays closed even though you have engineering access. It is bolted: bolts are a separate blocker from your ID card's access.
access-tut-try-bolted-door-tts = The door stays closed even though you have engineering access. It is bolted: bolts are a separate blocker from your ID card's access.

access-tut-press-signal-button-bubble = Press the signal button with [tutkeybind="UIClick"].
access-tut-press-signal-button-chat = The button retracts this airlock's bolts. Access and bolts are separate mechanisms.
access-tut-press-signal-button-tts = The button retracts this airlock's bolts. Access and bolts are separate mechanisms.

access-tut-open-bolted-door-bubble = The bolts are retracted. Open the airlock with [tutkeybind="UIClick"].
access-tut-open-bolted-door-chat = The airlock now accepts your engineering access. Opening it leads to the room that was unreachable by the direct route.
access-tut-open-bolted-door-tts = The airlock now accepts your engineering access. Opening it leads to the room that was unreachable by the direct route.

access-tut-finish-bubble = You reached the room that was inaccessible by the direct route.
access-tut-finish-chat = Check access first, then look for an authorised detour or an intended signal control. A locked or bolted door is not automatically an invitation to force it open.
access-tut-finish-tts = Check access first, then look for an authorised detour or an intended signal control. A locked or bolted door is not automatically an invitation to force it open.
